#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/application_scores.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays detailed information about application scores. The "
"lowest score is 0.0. The highest score is 10.0. The higher, the better. The "
"data is updated every full and half hour. Click on a value of interest, to "
"get a drilldown."
msgstr ""

#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/appserver/static/process_startup_duration.js:33
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays detailed information about application startup "
"performance."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/citrixsession_configuration_details.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays detailed information about applied Citrix HDX "
"policies and important active settings."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/browser_chrome.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays detailed information about browser resource usage by "
"process type. The most common process types are: browser (main process), tab "
"(rendering), GPU (GPU acceleration), extension (runs extensions), flash "
"(runs Flash)."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/machine_detail.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays detailed information about machine performance. The "
"terms 'machine' and 'host' are used interchangeably."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/machine_scores.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays detailed information about machine scores. The "
"lowest score is 0.0. The highest score is 10.0. The higher, the better. The "
"data is updated every full and half hour. Click on a value of interest, to "
"get a drilldown."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/citrix_machines.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays detailed information about machines for CVAD and "
"DaaS. Refer to the docs at https://docs.citrix.com/en-us/uberagent for "
"configuration instructions."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/process_netcomm.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays detailed information about network communication per "
"application, process, host, target or user."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/appserver/static/process_detail.js:160
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/process_detail.xml:5
msgid "This dashboard displays detailed information about process performance."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/appserver/static/process_startup_duration.js:55
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/process_startup_duration.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays detailed information about process startup "
"performance."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/citrix_published_apps.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays detailed information about published applications "
"and desktops for CVAD and DaaS. Refer to the docs at https://docs.citrix.com/"
"en-us/uberagent for configuration instructions."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/session_0_detail.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays detailed information about session 0 on all "
"machines. Sesssion 0 is the session that is used for services and user-mode "
"drivers."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/session_scores.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays detailed information about session scores. The "
"lowest score is 0.0. The highest score is 10.0. The higher, the better. The "
"data is updated every full and half hour. Click on a value of interest, to "
"get a drilldown. If there are two or more sessions for a user per machine, "
"the login time is added in parenthesis to the session to identify it more "
"easily."
msgstr ""

#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/appserver/static/application_input_delay.js:36
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays detailed information about the application input "
"delay."
msgstr ""

#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/appserver/static/application_input_delay.js:63
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays detailed information about the process input delay."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/machine_bugcheck.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays detailed information about three different types of "
"stop errors: blue screen of death, hard power off and random restart. A blue "
"screen is displayed when the system detects it cannot continue due to an "
"error condition and stops after collecting rudimentary information. A hard "
"power off happens when the user presses and holds the power button for at "
"least 4 seconds. A random restart may be due to power loss or a hard hang; "
"in either case the system cannot generate a blue screen any more."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/session_user_detail.xml:5
msgid "This dashboard displays detailed information about user sessions."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/browser_webappperf.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays detailed information for page loads and background "
"data transfers (XMLHttpRequests and web socket handshake requests). Data is "
"collected via browser extensions, which must be installed in addition to the "
"endpoint agent. \"Tab URL\" stands for the URL entered in the browser's "
"address bar; \"Request URL\" stands for an address the browser exchanged "
"data with."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/single_citrixadc_inventory.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays details for a NetScaler. Please note that inventory "
"information is only collected once per 24 hour period by default. uberAgent "
"collects inventory data from the primary as well as secondary NetScaler."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/single_boot_duration.xml:5
msgid "This dashboard displays information about a specific boot process."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/application_usage.xml:5
msgid "This dashboard displays information about actual application usage."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/application_errors.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays information about application errors (crashes and "
"hangs)."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/boot_delays.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays information about applications, services and drivers "
"that caused boot delays. The events that are processed here are generated "
"only when a delay occurs. The data displayed here does not reflect typical "
"boot processes."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/standby_delays.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays information about applications, services and drivers "
"that caused delays while entering or resuming from standby. The events that "
"are processed here are generated only when a delay occurs. The data "
"displayed here does not reflect typical standby or resume processes."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/shutdown_delays.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays information about applications, services and drivers "
"that caused shutdown delays. The events that are processed here are "
"generated only when a delay occurs. The data displayed here does not reflect "
"typical shutdown processes."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/machine_storage.xml:5
msgid "This dashboard displays information about disk drives and volumes."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/citrixadc_gateway.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays information about gateways on NetScalers monitored "
"with uberAgent. uberAgent only collects performance data from the primary "
"NetScaler."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/machine_macoserrors.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays information about kernel panics. These occur when "
"the operating system's kernel encounters an error from which it cannot "
"safely recover."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/windows_performance_counters.xml:12
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays information about performance counters collected on "
"Windows-based endpoints. Please note that performance counter metrics are "
"not enabled by default."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/application_netissues.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays information about reconnections, retransmissions and "
"failed TCP network connections. It can be used to identify application "
"misconfigurations, missing firewall rules or network and service outages."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/application_input_delay.xml:5
msgid "This dashboard displays information about the application input delay."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/boot_duration.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays information about the duration of system boots. A "
"boot process starts when Windows is loading and is finished when the desktop "
"is displayed and the load has dropped to 20%."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/shutdown_duration.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays information about the duration of system shutdowns."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/standby_duration.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays information about the duration of system standby and "
"resume processes."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/session_logoff_time.xml:5
msgid "This dashboard displays information about the duration of user logoffs."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/session_logon_time.xml:5
msgid "This dashboard displays information about the duration of user logons."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/user_input_delay.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays information about the input delay for user sessions."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/licensing_status.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays information about the licensing status of uberAgent. "
"It can only display information about licenses that are in use. If you have "
"licenses on your machines that are not currently used they will not appear "
"here."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/outlook_plugin_load.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays information about the load performance of Microsoft "
"Outlook plugins."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/machine_smbclient.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays information about the performance of SMB connections "
"to shares on the network."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/data_volume.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays information about the volume of data generated by "
"uberAgent. It is based on data from license_usage.log, stored in the "
"_internal index on the Splunk license master. Score indexes are not counted "
"towards Splunk licensing and can therefore not be displayed here.  If this "
"dashboard is empty, configure forwarding of the license master's _internal "
"index to your indexers. In larger implementations the data volume cannot be "
"determined per individual host due to squashing. Please note that enabling "
"ESA also increases the UXM data volume because additional fields are "
"populated in UXM sourcetypes, too."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/appserver/static/application_ui_delays.js:99
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/application_ui_delays.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays information about times of unresponsiveness, i.e. "
"when application user interfaces do not react to user input. Events are "
"generated every time applications do not process window messages for 200 ms "
"(or longer)."
msgstr ""

#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/appserver/static/application_ui_delays.js:38
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays information about times of unresponsiveness, i.e. "
"when processes do not react to user input. Events are generated every time "
"processes do not handle window messages for 200 ms (or longer)."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/browser_usage.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays information about web app as well as browser usage. "
"Data is collected via browser extensions, which must be installed in "
"addition to the endpoint agent."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/citrixadc_inventory.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays inventory information about the NetScalers monitored "
"with uberAgent. uberAgent collects inventory data from the primary as well "
"as secondary NetScaler."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/machine_inventory.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays inventory information about the endpoints monitored "
"with uberAgent."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/application_inventory.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays inventory information about the installed "
"applications."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/update_inventory.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays inventory information about the installed software "
"updates. The Windows 10 OS build number reflects a machine's update state in "
"a single number."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/machine_networkconfig.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays network configuration information about the "
"endpoints monitored with uberAgent."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/citrixadc_performance.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays performance information about NetScaler appliances "
"monitored with uberAgent. uberAgent only collects performance data from the "
"primary NetScaler."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/single_citrixadc_virtual_server_performance.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays performance information about virtual servers and "
"bound services as well as service groups. uberAgent only collects "
"performance data from the primary NetScaler."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/citrixadc_virtual_server_performance.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays performance information about virtual servers on "
"NetScalers monitored with uberAgent. uberAgent only collects performance "
"data from the primary NetScaler."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/sbc_sizing.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays relevant information for sizing server-based "
"computing farms (RDS/XenApp)."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/single_update_inventory.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays the install count of a specific update over time. It "
"also shows detailed information about each installation. Please note that "
"inventory information is only collected once per 24 hour period by default."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/single_application_inventory.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays the installed versions of a specific application "
"over time. It also shows detailed information about each installation. "
"Please note that inventory information is only collected once per 24 hour "
"period by default."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/single_machine_inventory.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays the number of application installations over time. "
"It also shows detailed information about each installed application and each "
"installed software update. Please note that inventory information is only "
"collected once per 24 hour period by default."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/browser_ie.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard displays the resources consumed per website. Each site's "
"performance is calculated across all user sessions and instances of Internet "
"Explorer."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/analyze_timechart.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard lets you interactively analyze any filtered subset of your "
"data over time."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/user_profile_overview.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard offers a comprehensive analysis of user profiles. It features "
"four panels displaying the top 10 profiles by size in MB, profile container "
"disk size in MB at logon, number of large files, and total file count. "
"Additionally, a data table provides a detailed breakdown of all logons in "
"the selected time range, including profile sizes and related information."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/citrixsession_insights.xml:4
msgid ""
"This dashboard provides an overview of typical performance patterns across "
"your Citrix environment. By comparing current behavior with historical "
"trends, it helps you quickly identify user experience degrading activity and "
"gain insight into system performance over time."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/machine_uptime.xml:5
msgid "This dashboard shows each host's uptime (days since last boot)."
msgstr ""

#. description
#: /opt/splunk/etc/apps/uberAgent/default/data/ui/views/uberagent_versions.xml:5
msgid ""
"This dashboard shows which uberAgent versions are active on the endpoints."
msgstr ""

